                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="484743" author="sergey" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2026 06:20:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adilger&quot;&gt;adilger&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is based on the LQA code, but it is implemented for regular project quotas as well as for LQA.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As it based on LQA code, I&apos;m waiting when the main LQA patches will be landed to master before sending that. So I&apos;ll push it as soon as &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61351,&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61351,&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61284,&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61284&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61239/42&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61239/42&lt;/a&gt; will be landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="484739" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2026 05:30:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=scherementsev&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;scherementsev&quot;&gt;scherementsev&lt;/a&gt;, did you implement this transfer of the quota limits on statfs to the MDT as part of LQA?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="472438" author="adilger" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2025 18:01:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It appears that the &lt;tt&gt;quotactl_ioctl()&lt;/tt&gt; call in &lt;tt&gt;ll_statfs_project()&lt;/tt&gt; is itself being split into a per-OST/MDT quota RPC to get the usage information, so it would be possible to push this down into the LOV/LOV (or OSC/MDC) code to fetch the quota usage for each target at statfs time and add it into the returned result. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One complexity is that the project quota &quot;statfs&quot; (and its cache) should not affect the cached real statfs data, so the quota info needs to be stored separately from actual statfs cache. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
